manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: FULL COLOR, 120° ULTRA WIDE ANGLE FORCE FLOW LIGHTING EFFECT The full range, 120° ultra wide angle luminous area at the top emits colorful bright light. The color of the light changes smoothly to provide gamers with an unparalleled visual feast, no matter it is day or night.

PURSUING THE PERFECT REVOLUTION The R on the heat spreader represents Revolution. The heat spreader is built with a lighter and thinner metal material. The hollow “R” design is very stereoscopic and matches with the ultra wide angle luminous area.

INCREASED TRANSMITTING PERFORMANCE Customized JEDEC RC 2.0 circuit board completely releases the transmission of memory module, and offers players the ultimate sensation of overclocking and a highly stable overclocking memory module.

ASYMMETRIC MINIMALIST DESIGN The one-piece, geometric line design makes the heat spreader look simple but energetic, and the Cubist style in the new art movement is also presented, which is a perfect combination of technology and aesthetics.

Supports Variety Kinds of Controlled Software The software allows users to control lighting effects and synchronization with DELTA RGB memory module. It creates unique, dazzling color aesthetics and offers a brilliant RGB system!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The TEAMGROUP T-Force Delta RGB DDR4 16GB kit is not just about raw performance; it's a showstopper in terms of aesthetics. Operating at a swift 3200MHz with a CAS latency of 16 (CL16), it delivers a responsive and efficient performance, perfect for gaming and multitasking. However, what truly steals the spotlight is its stunning RGB lighting.The white heat spreader design, in addition to giving a sleek and sophisticated appearance, sets the stage for a mesmerizing RGB light show. The Delta RGB lighting system is nothing short of a visual feast. The colors are vibrant, and the customization options are extensive. Syncing seamlessly with other RGB components through motherboard software, it transforms my rig into a dynamic work of art. The RGs are not just functional; they're a visual treat.Installation is a breeze, and the build quality is top-notch. The heat spreaders effectively dissipate heat, ensuring reliable performance during extended use. The 16GB capacity is ample for various applications, and the DDR4 technology ensures energy efficiency.In conclusion, the TEAMGROUP T-Force Delta RGB DDR4 16GB kit not only boosts your system's performance but also turns heads with its breathtaking RGB display. If you're in the market for RAM that not only works flawlessly but also makes your setup look like a dream, this kit is a must-have. The RGBs are not just pretty; they're the life of the party in your PC.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars must adjust BIOS to get 3200
reviews.reviewText: I got the 64gb kit at 3200, overall it's really nice. Dual rank, really nice blending with the RGB colors, slightly larger in physical size than the RAM i replaced. Had to go into BIOS and enable XMP2 to get the full 3200, but that's normal, just thought i'd mention it for those who just slap the RAM in and call it good. Largely that's all you gotta do. Helped out with games, i ran BeamNG on max settings and watched the machine start using up the memory. It ran great for hours. For Adobe Premier, this opened up my machine for both bigger projects without proxies, and higher resolution editing. nice and smooth now, less frustrating, and noticeably fewer crashes in premier if you can believe that. Fusion 360 also runs a lot better. Eventually i'll build a new rig using a new MOBO with DDR5, new GPU, maybe even a new case because why not, but i wanted to get a couple more years out of my current machine and this fit the bill.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Our computer savvy gamer son chose these memory modules to install in our new desk top computer. We replaced two 8GB modules with four 32GB. We have experienced no lag when gaming and you can have multiple screens open at one time without problem. The price point was good. Installation was basically plug and play. They are not unduly fragile. As a side note, we have a clear side to our desktop's tower and you can watch the modules light up and change color. VERY cool.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the price
reviews.reviewText: Great ram sticks that have a great capacity and speed and for the price also comes with RGB! Absolutely insane. It went really well with my full white rig and it's really good if you are on a budget and want some RGB on your ram.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing and Pretty
reviews.reviewText: I love these. They work great, they do their job, I highly recommend getting these if you're going to be downloading, playing high quality games, and having a lot of tabs open. If you're a streamer or just a gamer who likes playing games that take up alot of ram, I always recommend to get two 32 rams. People say it's a lot more than needed but personally, it's better to have it. They're really pretty and they work great. They don't get hot, they run amazing, it's everything it says it is.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not a low-profile RAM
reviews.reviewText: I recently bought the TEAMGROUP T-Force Delta RGB DDR4 32GB for my gaming PC and I have to say I'm pretty impressed. The RGB lighting is gorgeous and syncs well with my motherboard. The performance is also top-notch, with fast speeds and low latency. The installation was easy, and the packaging was nice.The only minor issue I have is that the RAM sticks are quite tall and they barely fit under my CPU cooler. I had to adjust the fan position a bit to make some room. It's not a big deal, but it would have been nice if they were a bit shorter or had a low-profile option.Overall, I'm very happy with my purchase and I would recommend this RAM to anyone looking for a reliable and stylish upgrade. I give it 4/5 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good looking ram
reviews.reviewText: I decided on getting 4x 8gb of ram for the aesthetics. Super easy to plug in, all worked seamlessly, and all sync'd up to my PC's RGB lighting.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stability, performance, and color
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I admit I bought this memory for its looks... but I enabled the 3600MT/s XMP profile and ran it through four full cycles of memtest86 (over 9 hours of testing) with 0 errors. SPD information reports the DRAM chips were made by SK Hynix. This is also true for the older sticks I bought a couple years ago. No trouble with them either.The default lighting (pictured in the video) is a nice effect that I can just sit and watch. Or I can use OpenRGB to turn the lights off at night.

I actually need to order another set to replace some old 2x8gb sticks.With that being said, the price is right regardless of it being on sale frequently and I definitely recommend this.
